[Student "S"]
{North is to play 3NT. East leads the \HQ.

Winners:   \S=0  \H=2  \D=2  \C=4  Total = 8

Needing one more winner you should see right away that it cannot come from \Hs, \Ds, or \Cs. That means you must hope that West has the \SA. Win the first \H, then play your 4 \C winners ending in dummy.

The moment of truth. You lead a small \S from dummy. West plays low and you play the \SK.

Unfortunately East takes your \SK with the \SA. He then plays another \H and you at least make 8 tricks but have no hope for a ninth one so you go down 1.

You probably thought since these Deals were all about finesses that they would work all of the time.

Welcome to the real world.}
[Play "W"]HQ

